OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1784758688
OL,3,CWes Streeting apologises for joke
OL,4,Cabout prisoner releases caught on
OL,5,Cmicrophone
OL,7,FIn the overheard conversation,
OL,8,FStreeting suggested to Mahmood that
OL,9,FNorris was "the enemy now" and "wants
OL,10,Fto let them all out".
OL,12,FStreeting said on X that the remark
OL,13,Fwas referencing a former joke shared
OL,14,Fbetween former Conservative prime
OL,15,Fminister Theresa May and ex-chancellor
OL,16,Fand home secretary Kenneth Clarke.
OL,18,FMay previously joked she "locked 'em
OL,19,Fup and he let 'em out" about her and
OL,20,FClarke's roles as home secretary and
OL,21,Fjustice secretary.
OL,26,@qD@LOUqD@ZO]qD@`OUrD@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1784758688
OL,3,CWes Streeting apologises for joke
OL,4,Cabout prisoner releases caught on
OL,5,Cmicrophone
OL,7,F"I hope everyone can see there was no
OL,8,Fill intent behind this ribbing of the
OL,9,Fnew Justice Secretary ` it was a
OL,10,Freference to an old May/Clarke joke,"
OL,11,FStreeting posted on X.
OL,13,F"But I appreciate these are very
OL,14,Fserious issues and am sorry for any
OL,15,Foffence inadvertently caused by this
OL,16,Fmoment of levity."
OL,18,FMahmood also said there was "no ill
OL,19,Fintent" about the "ribbing" of Norris.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUxD@RO]zD@]OU{D@GO]{D@SOU{D@
OL,26,A[O]
